snippet: Negotiators failed to reach an agreement over commercial protections for drug companies, leaving trade ministers to settle for a final round of talks on Sunday.
abstract: Trans-Pacific Partnership talks are extended for one final round as countries remain divided over disputes involving exclusive data rights on drugs and export of dairy products; negotiators are encouraged by scope of what has been agreed upon.
lead_paragraph: Negotiators failed to reach an agreement over commercial protections for drug companies, leaving trade ministers to settle for a final round of talks on Sunday.

headline.main: Trade Negotiations Stall Over Drugs and Dairy, Extending Talks Another Day
headline.print_headline: Trade Negotiations Stall Over Drugs and Dairy, Extending Talks Another Day
